[h1]Phobos' Operational Signals (POSnet)[/h1]

[b]Version 0.10.0 — Preview[/b]

A radio-driven procedural operations and market intelligence system for Project Zomboid Build 42.

[h2]Features[/h2]

[h3]POSnet Terminal[/h3]
[list]
[*] CRT-style terminal interface with 4 colour themes and resizable window
[*] Boot sequence, navigation panels, and screen stack architecture
[*] Desktop computer or portable computer connection via radio
[*] AZAS Frequency Index integration for dynamic per-world frequencies
[*] Signal strength system based on radio hardware (inverse square law)
[/list]

[h3]Operations & Missions[/h3]
[list]
[*] Procedural recon, delivery, and courier missions via BBS
[*] Investment opportunities with risk/reward simulation
[*] Mission negotiation and cancellation with reputation consequences
[*] Street address resolution and map waypoints via Paper Trails
[/list]

[h3]Market Intelligence[/h3]
[list]
[*] Commodity market simulation with 11 categories and 18 sub-categories
[*] Field reconnaissance produces category-specific item pricing
[*] Day-to-day price drift with supply/demand speculation
[*] Reputation-scaled price accuracy (5 tiers)
[*] Server-authoritative economy (multiplayer-safe from day one)
[/list]

[h3]Passive Reconnaissance Devices[/h3]
[list]
[*] Recon Camcorder — equippable, highest quality visual recon, requires VHS tape
[*] Field Survey Logger — equippable, environmental metadata, silent operation
[*] Scanner Radio — ALL vanilla radios enhanced with 4-tier passive scanning
[*] Data Calculator — compile raw data into higher-quality reports
[*] VHS-C tapes as physical intelligence storage (4 quality tiers)
[*] Tape crafting: repair, splice, improvise from scavenged materials
[*] VHS review at TV stations (CraftBench entity)
[/list]

[h3]Safety & Intelligence Quality[/h3]
[list]
[*] Danger detection — intel gathering and passive recon paused near threats
[*] 5-state context menu with colour-coded status and tooltips
[*] Dynamic note tooltips show category, observed items, and prices
[*] Journal/document system for in-game readable intelligence reports
[*] Intel gathering cooldown prevents location exploitation
[/list]

[h3]Data Persistence[/h3]
[list]
[*] World-scoped Global ModData for shared economy (6 containers)
[*] Tiny player-bound state (reputation, cash, watchlist, alerts)
[*] Building/mailbox caches externalized to flat files (scalable)
[*] Append-only event logs for auditing and admin analysis
[*] Capped rolling windows prevent save bloat
[*] Auto-migration from legacy data formats
[/list]

[h2]Dependencies[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Required:[/b] PhobosLib 1.40.0+ — [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3668598865]Steam Workshop[/url]
[*] [b]Required:[/b] AZAS Frequency Index
[*] [b]Optional:[/b] Phobos Chemistry Pathways (cross-mod market categories)
[*] [b]Optional:[/b] Paper Trails (street address resolution)
[/list]

[h2]Sandbox Options[/h2]
60+ configurable options covering broadcast intervals, mission parameters, market weighting, passive recon device behaviour, VHS tape mechanics, and economy tick settings.

[h2]Status[/h2]
Preview release — active development. Features are functional but expect changes.

